87-9; Rachold, V., Grigoriev, M.N., Are, F.E., Solomon, S., Reimnitz, E., Kassens, H., Antonow, M., Coastal erosion vs riverine sediment discharge in the Arctic Shelf seas (2000) Int. J. Earth Sci., 89, pp. 450-460; Romanovskii, N.N., Erosion-thermokarst basins in the northern marine plains of Yakutia and the New Siberian Islands (1961) Merzlotnye Issledovaniya. Sbornik Statey, 1, pp. 124-144; Romanovskii, N.N., Hubberten, H.-W., Gavrilov, A.V., Tumskoy, V.E., Kholodov, A.L., Permafrost of the east Siberian Arctic shelf and coastal lowlands (2004) Quat. Sci. Rev., 23, pp. 1359-1369; Romanovskii, N.N., Hubberten, H.-W., Gavrilov, A.V., Tumskoy, V.E., Tipenko, G.S., Grigoriev, M.N., Siegert, C., Thermokarst and land-ocean interactions, Laptev Sea region, Russia (2000) Permafrost Periglacial Process., 11, pp. 137-152; Schirrmeister, L., Grigoriev, M.N., Kutzbach, L., Wagner, D., Bolshiyanov, D., (2004) Russian-German Cooperation System Laptev Sea: The Expedition Lena-Anabar 2003, 489. , (eds.) Rep. Polar Mar. Res; Schirrmeister, L., Siegert, C., Kuznetsova, T., Kuzmina, S., Andreev, A., Kienast, F., Meyer, H., Bobrov, A., Paleoenvironmental and paleoclimatic records from permafrost deposits in the Arctic region of northern Siberia (2002) Quat. Int., 89, pp. 97-118; Sellmann, P.V., Brown, J., Lewellen, R.I., McKim, H.L., Merry, C.J., (1975) The Classification and Geomorphic Implications of Thaw Lakes on the Arctic Coastal Plain, Alaska, 344. , U.S. Army Cold Reg. Res. Engin. Lab. Res. Rep; Semiletov, I.P., Pipko, I.I., Pivovarov, N.Y., Popov, V.V., Zimov, S.A., Voropaev, Y.V., Daviodov, S.P., Atmospheric carbon emission from north Asian lakes: A factor of global significance (1996) Atmos. Environ., 30, pp. 1657-1671; Smith, L.C., MacDonald, G.M., Velichko, A.A., Beilman, D.W., Borisova, O.K., Frey, K.E., Kremenetski, K.V., Sheng, Y., Siberian peatlands-a net carbon sink and global methane source since the Early Holocene (2004) Science, 303, pp. 353-356; Soloviev, P.A., 